s","½ cinnamon quill","¼ tsp whole cloves","¼ tsp cardamom seeds (see Tips)","¼ tsp black mustard seeds","½ tsp black peppercorns","2 sprigs fresh curry leaves"]},{"title":"Lamb curry","content":["350 - 400 g lamb backstrap","200 g tri-colour quinoa","400 g water, plus extra for soaking","360 g brown onions, cut into quarters","2 garlic cloves","1 cm piece fresh ginger, peeled","20 g coconut oil","1 - 2 dried red chillies, trimmed and cut into halves","4 cardamom pods, crushed","1 sprig fresh curry leaves, leaves only","½ tsp paprika","¼ - 1 tsp chilli powder (optional)","¼ tsp ground turmeric","2 stalks fresh lemongrass, bruised and cut into halves","salt, to taste","350 g pumpkin, peeled and cut into pieces (2 cm)","200 g cherry tomatoes, cut into halves","100 g frozen baby peas","270 g coconut milk"]}],"id":"r150492","imageLink":"https:\/\/4.bp.blogspot.com\/-mqHj8KxgHag\/XZQFnBJVaXI\/AAAAAAAAb0w\/NxW1LsOr1pMTPDy2TaCpWIt6y-jAnyMlgCLcBGAsYHQ\/s1600\/0_7yfdz7ajSG3AOMdV.png","title":"Layered lamb curry","publishedAt":"2018-04-02T00:00:00Z","nutrition":{"protein":"43.5 g","fat":"26.7 g","uom":"per 1 portion","carbohydrates":"49.6 g","calories":"2668 kJ \/ 635 kcal"},"usefulItems":"sealable container, large bowl","hintsAndTricks":["You can buy cardamom seeds from Indian food stores or you can bruise cardamom pods and remove the seeds.","You can store the Sri Lankan curry powder in a sealable container in the pantry for up to 3 months."],"basicInfo":["easy","20m","1h","4 portions"]}